Key Match Events: Boston Celtics lost to Sacramento Kings 114-97 at home
Post-Match Reflections: Jaylen Brown stated, 'Tonight, we had some collapses... It's really no excuse, so we're gonna look at it and we're gonna figure it out. It's a long journey. I believe in this team. We've got a great group of guys, so we're gonna figure this out.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics dropped to 27-11 with the loss, second seed in the Eastern Conference, and have a 5-5 record in their last ten games. They will host the New Orleans Pelicans next.
